Data Analysis using Excel, Advanced Excel & Power BI
Duration: 40 Hours (40 Days × 1 Hour), Fees : 700 per student
Mode: Classroom / Online / Hybrid
________________________________________
Module 1: Excel Basics 
•	Introduction to Data Analysis & Excel Overview
•	Entering, Editing & Formatting Data
•	Sorting & Filtering Data
•	Basic Formulas (SUM, AVERAGE, COUNT)
•	Conditional Formatting & Data Cleaning
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 1 – Clean & Analyze Student Data)
Module 2: Excel Functions 
•	Text Functions (LEFT, RIGHT, MID, TRIM, CONCAT)
•	Date Functions (TODAY, NOW, DATEDIF, EOMONTH)
•	Logical Functions (IF, Nested IF, IFS)
•	Lookup Functions – VLOOKUP & HLOOKUP
•	INDEX + MATCH, XLOOKUP
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 2 – Employee Age & Salary Lookup)
Module 3: Advanced Excel 
•	Data Validation (Drop-downs, Error Messages)
•	Advanced Functions (SUMIFS, COUNTIFS, AVERAGEIFS)
•	INDIRECT, OFFSET Functions
•	Introduction to Pivot Tables
•	Pivot Charts, Slicers & Timelines
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 3 – Sales Analysis with Pivot Tables)
Module 4: Power Query & Dashboards 
•	Introduction to Power Query in Excel
•	Importing & Cleaning Data with Power Query
•	Data Visualization – Charts (Bar, Line, Pie, Combo)
•	Building an Interactive Excel Dashboard
Module 5: Power BI Basics 
•	Power BI Desktop Overview
•	Importing Data into Power BI
•	Data Modeling & Relationships
•	Power BI Visualizations (Bar, Line, Pie, Maps, Cards)
Module 6: Power BI Advanced 
•	Filters, Slicers, Drill-through, Bookmarks
•	Introduction to DAX (Measures vs Columns)
•	KPIs with DAX (Total Sales, Profit Margin %, Growth)
Module 7: Capstone Project 
•	End-to-End Data Analysis Project:
o	Import Data with Power Query
o	Clean & Transform Data
o	Analyze with Pivot Tables in Excel
o	Build Dashboards in Excel + Power BI
•	Final Presentation & Q&A
Student Deliverables
•	Daily hands-on practice files
•	3 Mini Projects (Excel cleaning, Lookup-based analysis, Pivot analysis)
•	1 Final Capstone Project (Excel + Power BI Dashboard)
•	LinkedIn and GitHub Profiles
•	Course Completion Certificate

 
R Programming with Data Analysis
Duration: 40 Hours (40 Days × 1 Hour) Fees : 700 per student
Mode: Classroom / Online / Hybrid
________________________________________
Module 1: Introduction to R & RStudio
•	Overview of R & RStudio (IDE)
•	Installing packages & managing libraries
•	Understanding R syntax & operators
•	Data types in R (numeric, character, factor, logical)
•	Vectors, Lists, Matrices, Data Frames
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 1 – Student Marks Data Exploration)
Module 2: Data Manipulation in R
•	Importing data (CSV, Excel, Web, Database)
•	Exploring datasets (head, tail, summary, str)
•	Data Cleaning – handling missing values, duplicates, outliers
•	Subsetting data with indexing & conditions
•	Merging, Joining, and Binding datasets
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 2 – Employee Salary Dataset Cleaning)
Module 3: R Functions & Programming Basics
•	Writing user-defined functions
•	Conditional statements (if, else, ifelse)
•	Loops (for, while, repeat)
•	Apply family functions (apply, lapply, sapply, tapply)
•	Introduction to dplyr for data manipulation (filter, select, mutate, summarise, group_by)
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 3 – Sales Transactions Aggregation)
Module 4: Data Visualization in R
•	Base R plotting (plot, hist, boxplot, barplot)
•	Customizing plots (colors, labels, themes)
•	Introduction to ggplot2
•	ggplot basics: aesthetics, geoms, facets
•	Building different charts: bar, line, scatter, histogram, density, boxplot
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 4 – Visualize Student Performance)
Module 5: Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
•	Descriptive statistics (mean, median, mode, sd, var, quantile)
•	Correlation & covariance
•	Crosstabs & frequency tables
•	Outlier detection (IQR, z-scores)
•	Feature transformation (log, scaling, normalization)
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 5 – EDA on Titanic Dataset)
Module 6: Introduction to Statistical Analysis in R
•	Probability distributions (normal, binomial, Poisson)
•	Hypothesis testing (t-test, chi-square, ANOVA)
•	Correlation & regression basics
•	Simple & multiple linear regression
•	Logistic regression (intro)
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 6 – Predicting Exam Pass/Fail)
Module 7: Capstone Project
End-to-End Data Analysis Project:
•	Import dataset into R
•	Clean & preprocess data using dplyr
•	Perform exploratory data analysis
•	Apply statistical models
•	Create meaningful visualizations with ggplot2
•	Present insights in an R Markdown / Shiny dashboard
Student Deliverables
•	Daily hands-on R scripts
•	5 Mini Projects (Data Cleaning, Aggregation, Visualization, EDA, Statistical Analysis)
•	1 Final Capstone Project (Full Data Analysis Workflow in R)
•	LinkedIn and GitHub Profiles, Course Completion Certificate
Python Data Analysis
Duration: 40 Hours (40 Days × 1 Hour) Fees : 700 per student
Mode: Classroom / Online / Hybrid
________________________________________
Module 1: Python Basics for Data Analysis
•	Introduction to Python & Jupyter Notebook
•	Python syntax, variables & data types
•	Lists, Tuples, Sets, Dictionaries
•	Conditional statements & loops
•	Functions & lambda functions
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 1 – Student Marks Data Exploration)
Module 2: Working with Data in Python
•	Importing datasets (CSV, Excel, SQL, JSON) with pandas
•	Exploring data: head, tail, info, describe
•	Data cleaning: missing values, duplicates, outliers
•	Data selection & indexing (loc, iloc)
•	Sorting, filtering, grouping (groupby)
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 2 – Employee Salary Dataset Cleaning)
Module 3: Data Manipulation with Pandas & Numpy
•	Introduction to NumPy arrays
•	Array operations & broadcasting
•	Aggregations & descriptive statistics
•	Vectorized operations for speed
•	Merging, joining, concatenating datasets with pandas
•	Pivot tables in pandas
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 3 – Sales Transactions Aggregation)
Module 4: Data Visualization in Python
•	Introduction to Matplotlib (line, bar, pie, histogram, scatter)
•	Customizing plots (labels, titles, colors, legends)
•	Introduction to Seaborn for statistical plots
•	Heatmaps, pairplots, boxplots, violin plots
•	Styling plots (themes, grids, annotations)
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 4 – Visualizing Student Performance)
Module 5: Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
•	Descriptive statistics with pandas & NumPy
•	Correlation, covariance, cross-tabulation
•	Feature scaling & transformations (log, normalization, standardization)
•	Outlier detection (IQR, Z-score)
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 5 – EDA on Titanic Dataset)
Module 6: Introduction to Statistics & Machine Learning in Python
•	Probability distributions with SciPy
•	Hypothesis testing (t-test, chi-square, ANOVA)
•	Linear regression with scikit-learn
•	Logistic regression basics
•	Model evaluation metrics (accuracy, precision, recall, F1, ROC-AUC)
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 6 – Predicting Exam Pass/Fail)
Module 7: Capstone Project
End-to-End Data Analysis Project using Python
•	Import dataset with pandas
•	Clean & preprocess data
•	Perform exploratory data analysis
•	Visualize with Matplotlib & Seaborn
•	Apply basic ML model (regression/classification)
•	Present insights in Jupyter Notebook
Student Deliverables
•	Daily Python scripts & notebooks
•	5 Mini Projects (Data Cleaning, Aggregation, Visualization, EDA, Statistical Analysis)
•	1 Final Capstone Project (Full Data Analysis Workflow in Python)
•	LinkedIn and GitHub Profiles
•	Course Completion Certificate 
Python Machine Learning
Duration: 40 Hours (40 Days × 1 Hour) Fees : 700 per student
Mode: Classroom / Online / Hybrid
________________________________________
Module 1: Introduction to Machine Learning
•	What is Machine Learning? Types (Supervised, Unsupervised, Reinforcement)
•	ML workflow: data → features → model → evaluation
•	Introduction to scikit-learn
•	Splitting data: train/test sets (train_test_split)
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 1 – Predicting Student Pass/Fail with Logistic Regression)
Module 2: Data Preprocessing for ML
•	Handling missing values (mean, median, mode, KNN imputation)
•	Encoding categorical variables (Label, One-Hot Encoding)
•	Feature scaling (Normalization, Standardization, MinMax)
•	Train/test split, cross-validation basics
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 2 – Preprocessing Titanic Dataset)
Module 3: Supervised Learning – Classification Models
•	Logistic Regression
•	Decision Trees
•	Random Forest Classifier
•	Support Vector Machines (SVM)
•	K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)
•	Model evaluation: accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, ROC-AUC
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 3 – Predicting Loan Approval)
Module 4: Supervised Learning – Regression Models
•	Linear Regression (simple & multiple)
•	Polynomial Regression
•	Decision Tree Regressor
•	Random Forest Regressor
•	Evaluation metrics: MAE, MSE, RMSE, R² score
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 4 – Predicting House Prices)
Module 5: Unsupervised Learning
•	K-Means Clustering
•	Hierarchical Clustering
•	Principal Component Analysis (PCA)
•	Dimensionality reduction & visualization
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 5 – Customer Segmentation)
Module 6: Model Optimization & Advanced Topics
•	Bias-variance trade-off
•	Cross-validation & GridSearchCV
•	Feature importance & selection
•	Ensemble methods: Bagging, Boosting (AdaBoost, Gradient Boosting, XGBoost intro)
•	Introduction to Neural Networks (MLPClassifier, MLPRegressor)
•	Hands-on Practice (Mini Project 6 – Credit Card Fraud Detection)
Module 7: Capstone Project
End-to-End Machine Learning Project using Python
•	Import & preprocess dataset
•	Apply EDA & feature engineering
•	Train multiple ML models
•	Compare performance with metrics & visualizations
•	Select best model & finalize pipeline
•	Present insights in Jupyter Notebook
Student Deliverables
•	Daily Jupyter Notebooks with ML exercises
•	6 Mini Projects (Classification, Regression, Clustering, PCA, Ensemble, Fraud Detection)
•	1 Capstone ML Project (End-to-End Model Development & Evaluation)
•	LinkedIn and GitHub Profiles
•	Course Completion Certificate
